---
import { ProjectPreview } from "@/components"
import Main from "@/layouts/main.astro"
import Bull from "@/components/Bull.astro"
import Kbd from "@/components/Kbd.astro"
---

<Main
  htmlClass="pager-page"
  title="pager - share a line of thought"
  description="pager is a tiny macOS app that feels like a note you pass to your crush in class."
  favicon="/pager/pager-logo.svg"
>
  <div class="max-w-md">
    <div class="h-4 sm:h-12"></div>
    <a href="/" class="link underline-offset-4"><span style="text-decoration: none !important;" class="inline-block no-underline mr-1.5 font-mono">&lt;-</span>back to home</a>
    <div class="h-8 sm:h-24"></div>

  <div class="w-full flex justify-start pr-4 -ml-1.5">
    <img
      src="/pager/pager-logo.svg"
      alt="pager app logo"
      class="w-full max-w-20 aspect-square"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="h-8 sm:h-12"></div>

  <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-end gap-2 sm:gap-0">
    <h1 class="font-semibold text-foreground text-lg">
      pager
    </h1><span class="mx-2 hidden sm:inline-block text-muted-foreground">&middot;</span>
    <h2>
      share a line of thought
    </h2>
  </div>

  <div class="h-5 md:h-6"></div>

  <div class="space-y-3 max-w-md">
    <p>
      a single note that sits in your menu bar, synced with someone that matters to you.
    </p><p>
      share a thought, a joke, a link. share a moment.
    </p><p>
      no history, no feed, no notifications: just a quiet, shared thought that lives in your periphery.
    </p><p>
      pager feels like a note that you pass to your crush in class. like a post-it in your lunchbox, saying &ldquo;i love you&rdquo; or &ldquo;have a wonderful day&rdquo;.
  </p></div>

  <div class="h-5 md:h-6"></div>

  <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-2 sm:gap-0">
    <p>
      <span class="font-semibold mr-2 sm:mr-1">curious?</span>
      <a href="/pager/Pager.zip" download class="link">download pager for free</a>
    </p>
  </div>
  <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-2 text-sm">(only macOS)</p>

  <div class="h-5 md:h-6"></div>
  <div class="h-px bg-border w-full"></div>
  <div class="h-5 md:h-6"></div>

  <div class="space-y-3">
    <p class="font-semibold">note on installation</p>

    <p>to install, download <Kbd>Pager.zip</Kbd> from the link above, unzip it, and drag <Kbd>Pager.app</Kbd> to Applications.</p>

    <p>while pager is in beta, macOS will complain when you open it ("Apple could not verify…"). close that dialog (don't move it to Trash).</p>

  <p>open <span class="font-medium">System Settings → Privacy & Security</span>, scroll down, and click
    <span class="font-medium">Open Anyway</span> next to "Pager.app was blocked…".</p>

    <p>that's it; pager will live in your menu bar (it shows up as 📟). on first run it asks you to
    create a pager (send the code to your BFF, lover, or sibling) or join with a code you received.
    enable <span class="font-medium">Launch at login</span> so it's always there.</p></div>



  </div></Main>
